nginx notes

nginx installed through yum on our CentOS instance is an old version and when a newer version is added to the repo it still has errors.

To install nginx from scratch

Grab the dependency: curl -c - -O ftp://ftp.csx.cam.ac.uk/pub/software/programming/pcre/pcre-8.21.tar.gz
Grab the source: curl -c - -O http://nginx.org/download/nginx-1.0.13.tar.gz

./configure --prefix=/etc/nginx/ --sbin-path=/usr/sbin/nginx --pid-path=/tmp/nginx.pid --error-log-path=/tmp/nginx.error.log --http-log-path=/tmp/nginx.access.log --user=nginx --group=nginx --conf-path=/etc/nginx/nginx.conf --with-pcre=/tmp/pcre-8.21/
make
sudo make install

For more details visit these links:
  http://wiki.nginx.org/RedHatNginxInitScript
  http://wiki.nginx.org/Install#Building_Nginx_From_Source

Copy the nginx.conf file to the /etc/nginx/ directory
Copy ../init.d/nginx to the /etc/init.d/ directory

issue 'apps/search/boot.sh'
issue 'services/catalogue/boot.sh'
issue 'service nginx start'
